\[
\frac{1}{2m}
= \frac{1}{2m}\cdot\frac{4mn}{4mn}
= \frac{4mn}{8m^2n},
\]

we get

\[
\frac{1}{2m}+\frac{7}{8m^2n}
=\frac{4mn}{8m^2n}+\frac{7}{8m^2n}
=\frac{4mn+7}{8m^2n}\,.
\]

To subtract, write both over the common denominator \((w+4)(w-2)\):  
\[
\frac{w+2}{w+4}-\frac{w}{w-2}
=\frac{(w+2)(w-2)-w(w+4)}{(w+4)(w-2)}
=\frac{w^2-4-(w^2+4w)}{(w+4)(w-2)}
=\frac{-4w-4}{(w+4)(w-2)}
=-\frac{4(w+1)}{(w+4)(w-2)}.
\]
Domain: \(w\neq -4,2\).

