To combine the terms, note that \(c^2-4=(c-2)(c+2)\).  Rewrite each fraction over the common denominator \((c-2)(c+2)\):

\[
\frac{c}{c+2}
=\frac{c(c-2)}{(c+2)(c-2)}
=\frac{c^2-2c}{(c-2)(c+2)}, 
\]

\[
\frac{5}{c-2}
=\frac{5(c+2)}{(c-2)(c+2)}
=\frac{5c+10}{(c-2)(c+2)},
\]

\[
\frac{10c}{c^2-4}
=\frac{10c}{(c-2)(c+2)}.
\]

So the sum is
\[
\frac{c^2-2c}{(c-2)(c+2)}
+\frac{5c+10}{(c-2)(c+2)}
-\frac{10c}{(c-2)(c+2)}
=\frac{c^2-2c+5c+10-10c}{(c-2)(c+2)}
=\frac{c^2-7c+10}{(c-2)(c+2)}.
\]
Factor the numerator:
\[
c^2-7c+10=(c-5)(c-2),
\]
so
\[
\frac{c^2-7c+10}{(c-2)(c+2)}
=\frac{(c-5)(c-2)}{(c-2)(c+2)}
=\frac{c-5}{c+2},
\]
with the restriction \(c\neq2,-2\). 

