First factor and rewrite the second term:

\[
\frac{-5n-5}{n^2+n-6}
=\frac{-5(n+1)}{(n+3)(n-2)}, 
\qquad
\frac{n+1}{2-n}
=\frac{n+1}{-(n-2)}
=-\frac{n+1}{\,n-2\,}.
\]

Put both over the common denominator \((n+3)(n-2)\):

\[
\frac{-5(n+1)}{(n+3)(n-2)}
\;-\;\frac{n+1}{\,n-2\,}
=\frac{-5(n+1)}{(n+3)(n-2)}
-\frac{(n+1)(n+3)}{(n+3)(n-2)}.
\]

Combine the numerators:

\[
\frac{-5(n+1)-(n+1)(n+3)}{(n+3)(n-2)}
=\frac{(n+1)\bigl(-5-(n+3)\bigr)}{(n+3)(n-2)}
=\frac{-(n+1)(n+8)}{(n+3)(n-2)}.
\]

So the simplified result is

\[
\boxed{
-\frac{(n+1)(n+8)}{(n+3)(n-2)}, 
\quad n\neq2,-3.
}
\]

To combine the fractions, use the common denominator \((x-2)(x+5)\).  We have

\[
\frac{4}{x-2}+\frac{3}{x+5}
=\frac{4(x+5)+3(x-2)}{(x-2)(x+5)}
=\frac{4x+20+3x-6}{(x-2)(x+5)}
=\frac{7x+14}{(x-2)(x+5)}
=\frac{7(x+2)}{(x-2)(x+5)}.
\]

