To combine the terms, write 2 as \(\tfrac{2(q+4)}{q+4}\) and get a common denominator:

\[
\frac{2q+7}{q+4} - 2
= \frac{2q+7}{q+4} - \frac{2(q+4)}{q+4}
= \frac{2q+7 - (2q+8)}{q+4}
= \frac{2q + 7 - 2q - 8}{q+4}
